====================================================================================================================================================================================================================================

üìÅ 1. File and Directory Commands

1Ô∏è‚É£ pwd
‚Üí Prints the current working directory (your current location in the file system).

2Ô∏è‚É£ ls
‚Üí Lists all files and directories in the current location.

3Ô∏è‚É£ ls -a
‚Üí Lists all files, including hidden files (those starting with a dot .).

4Ô∏è‚É£ ls -l
‚Üí Displays detailed information about files (permissions, owner, size, date).

5Ô∏è‚É£ ls -lt
‚Üí Lists files sorted by modification time (latest first).

6Ô∏è‚É£ ls -ltr
‚Üí Lists files sorted by modification time (oldest first).

7Ô∏è‚É£ cd foldername
‚Üí Change directory to the specified folder.

8Ô∏è‚É£ cd ..
‚Üí Move one level up (to the parent directory).

9Ô∏è‚É£ mkdir foldername
‚Üí Creates a new directory (folder).

10Ô∏è‚É£ rmdir foldername
‚Üí Removes an empty directory.

11Ô∏è‚É£ rm file.txt
‚Üí Deletes a file.

12Ô∏è‚É£ rm -r foldername
‚Üí Deletes a folder and all its contents (recursive remove).

13Ô∏è‚É£ cp file1 file2
‚Üí Copies file1 to file2 (creates a duplicate).

14Ô∏è‚É£ cp -r folder1 folder2
‚Üí Copies folders recursively.

15Ô∏è‚É£ mv file1 file2
‚Üí Moves or renames files or directories.

16Ô∏è‚É£ touch file.txt
‚Üí Creates a new empty file.

17Ô∏è‚É£ cat file.txt
‚Üí Displays file contents in the terminal.

18Ô∏è‚É£ head -n 10 file.txt
‚Üí Shows the first 10 lines of a file.

19Ô∏è‚É£ tail -n 10 file.txt
‚Üí Shows the last 10 lines of a file.

20Ô∏è‚É£ less file.txt
‚Üí Opens file content in a scrollable view.

====================================================================================================================================================================================================================================

‚úçÔ∏è 2. File Editing Commands

21Ô∏è‚É£ nano file.txt
‚Üí Opens file in the Nano text editor (easy to use).

22Ô∏è‚É£ vim file.txt
‚Üí Opens file in the Vim editor (advanced text editor).

üîç 3. Search and Locate Commands

23Ô∏è‚É£ grep "word" file.txt
‚Üí Searches for a specific word or pattern in a file.

24Ô∏è‚É£ find . -name "file.txt"
‚Üí Searches for a file by name from the current directory.

====================================================================================================================================================================================================================================

‚öôÔ∏è 4. File Permissions and Ownership

25Ô∏è‚É£ ls -l
‚Üí Shows file permissions (read, write, execute).

26Ô∏è‚É£ chmod 777 file.txt
‚Üí Changes file permission to full access for everyone.

27Ô∏è‚É£ chown user file.txt
‚Üí Changes ownership of a file.

====================================================================================================================================================================================================================================

üíª 5. System and Process Management

28Ô∏è‚É£ top
‚Üí Displays running processes and system usage in real-time.

29Ô∏è‚É£ ps aux
‚Üí Shows a snapshot of all running processes.

30Ô∏è‚É£ kill process_id
‚Üí Terminates a process using its process ID.

====================================================================================================================================================================================================================================

üíæ 6. Disk and Memory Usage

31Ô∏è‚É£ df -h
‚Üí Shows disk usage in human-readable format.

32Ô∏è‚É£ du -sh foldername
‚Üí Shows the size of a folder.

33Ô∏è‚É£ free -h
‚Üí Displays memory (RAM) usage.

====================================================================================================================================================================================================================================

üë• 7. User and System Info

34Ô∏è‚É£ who
‚Üí Lists all currently logged-in users.

35Ô∏è‚É£ whoami
‚Üí Displays your current username.

36Ô∏è‚É£ date
‚Üí Displays current system date and time.

37Ô∏è‚É£ date +%D
‚Üí Shows date in short format (MM/DD/YY).

38Ô∏è‚É£ date +%T
‚Üí Shows current time only.

39Ô∏è‚É£ hostname
‚Üí Displays the system hostname.

40Ô∏è‚É£ uname -a
‚Üí Displays system and kernel information.

====================================================================================================================================================================================================================================

üßπ 8. Miscellaneous Commands

41Ô∏è‚É£ clear
‚Üí Clears the terminal screen.

42Ô∏è‚É£ history
‚Üí Shows the list of previously used commands.

43Ô∏è‚É£ exit
‚Üí Logs out or closes the terminal.

